*nvidia-kernel-1.0.2880-r1 (29 Apr 2002)

  8 May 2002; Jon Nelson <jnelson@gentoo.org>
  	nvidia-kernel-1.0.2880-r1.ebuild :
        
  Make sure to usr KERNDIR=/usr/src/linux
  /usr/src/linux should be a symlink pointing to the real sources,
  which may lie outside /usr/src.  KV is set appropriately
  in any case by more recent versions of portage.

  3 May 2002; Arcady Genkin <agenkin@thpoon.com>
	nvidia-kernel-1.0.2800-r1.ebuild :

  Make sure that Portage *does* set KV to something; bail out otherwise. ;^)
	
  29 Apr 2002; Daniel Robbins <drobbins@gentoo.org>: Changed NV_KV to KV and
  added a Portage dependency to ensure that KV is available.  Should fix some
  build problems.

*nvidia-kernel-1.0.2880 (7 Apr 2002)

  7 Apr 2002; M.Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> nvidia-kernel-1.0.2880.ebuild
  Fixed all the spaces.
